,Recommended,485450,24100061,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,Kunovega,"This is a pretty simple puzzle game that might be worth $1 some day.It's marred by some bugs though.1) Sound keeps forgetting what I have it set to. It randomly jumps from the volume I have it set at to blasting out my ear drums (with headphones on)2) to-hit boxes are not lined up well. the entire game relies on you moving with precision to avoid obstacles. What makes it hard is that the obstacles hit box is larger than the graphic so I find myself getting revealed by things that aren't actually touching me (the game pauses to show you your failure for a second ~ it's annoying to see that you failed and the thing that supposedly touched you isn't even touching you)This is a game I wish I could mark as neutral rather than thumbs up or down, at least in its current state.Thing is, it's also early access. So I'm going to give it the benefit of the doubt and push my neutral to a thumbs up rather than down because hopefully the developers will continue tweaking this before calling it a final release.Anyway. Not much point in giving a deep review on this. Look at the screenshots and video. That is the game in a nutshell. You are a ninja and you avoid being detected. But don't expect to be fighting or doing anything other than avoid detection. This is a puzzle game and your character could be a ball avoiding circles and cones and it would play the same as you being a ninja avoiding cameras and what not.So, bottom line I got this for 50% off with a coupon from making a badge. It's a neat little puzzle game for $1 or less and hopefully the devs will polish it a bit further while its still in early access."
