,Recommended,485450,31161355,Posted: 15 April,all,aeko,"I bought this game on sale last weekend for about 39 or 49 cents, I'm not very sure to be fair. I just want to make it clear that it was a ""cheap pack"". I got the chance to try it out today and I must say it is a very nice game with about 25 levels plus some extra levels and a Halloween scene on the side which I also completed. It begins as easy, in my opinion. You can learn very quickly the mechanics on the game which are simple and effective. However, once you reach about level 18 or so, it begins to get a tad bit more complicated and you might have to give it more than one try to pass on to the next level. The soundtrack for me is quite nice as well, no complains. The only negative aspect I found, which some may disagree, is that the sensors are ""too tuned"". So, what I'm trying to say, is that in my opinion, sometimes when you are not supposed to get caught by a camera or by a laser, you will be. But I can live with that.Also: there's a second episode which unfortunately I could not play and later I figured out that I had to buy some sort of expansion in order to play it. It was not of my understandings when I first bought the game and I was a little bit disappointed by that fact, I'm still considering on buying it if it goes on a good sale.All in all, I give this game 8/10 taking in consideration the following aspects:-Challenge-Price-Achievements-Steam trade cards-FunI recommend it to everyone who is trying to relax and play a nice little game for a couple hours in order to complete it, paying just a small amount in order to do so."
,Recommended,485450,23462541,"Posted: 8 June, 2016",all,NME Plays,"I initially had less than favorable things to say about the game with the early access version, however, going back and taking a look at all the improvements the developer has made, I have changed my opinion.Most, if not all, of the complaints I had about the original have been addressed and either removed or fixed.  The game operates much more fairly and smoothly now.  Checkpoints are there to keep you from repeating the same tedious obstacles too many times.  Guards act the way you'd expect guards to act.  You can MGS your way through some stuff hiding in a box even.My only real complaints now are really personal preference things.  It's odd that some boxes move, and some don't.  There are 3 different types of boxes, but that doesn't tell you if they're movable or not.  Just, how easily they may move if they do.  It feels strange, but it's minor.  I also pushed a box I should have been able to enter through a wall, which made it impossible to get a bonus computer.  Again, it's a minor bug, but it may result in level breaking consequences.I said before that this game has a lot of potential to be a lot more fun than it is, and the developer proved beyond a shadow of a doubt they are willing to put the effort in to make it just that.  This is an excellent update on what was delivered in Early Access and I'm very happy to do a 180 on my feelings for the game.  The price tag asked on this game is absolutely fair, and I'm really excited to see more from this developer."
